import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='lat', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['lat'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['lat'].median()))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of latitudes in the U-District dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    plt.axvline(x=data['lat'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean: {data['lat'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average latitude in the U-District dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt
